## Undocumented Behaviors — Found in RTL, Not in Manual

> This table will expand. These are CTP parameters where the manual gives insufficient information and we had to verify behavior from RTL source code. Each entry is a potential documentation gap worth flagging upstream.

| Parameter | Value | What Manual Says | What RTL Shows | RTL Source |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|----------------|------------|
| `TRAP_ON_RESERVED_INSTRUCTION` | `true` | `exceptions_interrupts.rst` mentions FPU-disabled traps implicitly — side-note only | Also traps on disabled PULP extensions, undefined opcodes, and any instruction not explicitly decoded (catch-all default case) | `cv32e40p_decoder.sv:2977` — `default : illegal_insn_o = 1'b1` |
| `TRAP_ON_UNIMPLEMENTED_CSR` | `true` | Not documented — spec default (silent zero return) would be assumed | CSR address validation is a case statement; unlisted addresses hit default and trap — opposite of spec default | `cv32e40p_decoder.sv:2978` — `default : csr_illegal = 1'b1` |
| `TRAP_ON_ILLEGAL_WLRL` | `false` | Not documented — field descriptions give no indication either way | Cannot trap on write values: decoder runs in ID stage, write data only available in EX stage; RTL silently masks illegal bits instead | `cv32e40p_cs_registers.sv:340-1023` — masking logic, no exception path |

